<p><img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/a/a4/Flag_of_the_United_States.svg/46px-Flag_of_the_United_States.svg.png"> Robert Glenn "Robbie" Lawler (born March 20, 1982) is an American professional mixed martial artist currently competing in the Welterweight division of the Ultimate Fighting Championship, where he is the current UFC Welterweight Champion. A professional competitor since 2001, Lawler is also a former EliteXC Middleweight Champion, and has formerly competed in Strikeforce, PRIDE, and the IFL. As of December 10, 2014, Lawler has been the UFC Welterweight Champion and #6 pound-for-pound in official UFC rankings.</p>